Sample Size

We count 1277 people who initialized the survey. 53.2% of them failed to complete the survey which leaves us with 598 complete observations. The following visualization shows that most of the dropouts did not manage to read through the instructions. After having read them, few people dropped out.

Figure 1: Dropouts by Page.

Figure 2: Complete Observations over Time.

482 participants state that they understood the instructions. 116 say that they did not.1

Time

The time spent on every decision looks as follows. Intuitively, the pattern makes sense as respondents learn from round 1 to 6. Round 7 exposes the respondents to the forecast, which needs some time to process.

Figure 3: Average Time Spent for each Decision per Round.

The median time to complete the survey was 16 minutes.

The reported indices stem from matching probabilities. To check whether respondents stated the matching probabilities diligently, we expect them to exhibit some variance at the individual level. It turns out that there are some people (32) who enter the same matching probability each and every time. The following graph visualizes each respondents standard deviation over all 12 rounds as a histogram:

Figure 4: Histogram: Standard Deviation of individual Decisions (across all rounds)

Sample Properties

The vast majority (371 out of 599 participants) is male. 52 participants have no interest in vaccinations and 490 are vaccinated (at least once) already. The average participant is 47 years of age.

Figure 6: Histogram: Age Distribution.

  1. 11 stated that they did not understand the game at all.
